ğŸ¤– AI Guru â€“ SLM-Powered Quiz Generation System

AI Guru is a local AI-powered educational platform that generates and delivers Data Structures & Algorithms (DSA) multiple-choice questions using a Small Language Model (SLM) combined with dataset-based retrieval.
The system is designed for offline execution, data privacy, and fast response time, making it ideal for academic and low-resource environments.

ğŸš€ Project Overview

Traditional AI learning platforms rely on cloud-based Large Language Models (LLMs), which introduce challenges such as high cost, latency, and privacy concerns.
AI Guru addresses these issues by leveraging a locally deployed Small Language Model (TinyLlama-1.1B) integrated with a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) approach.

The application is built using Streamlit and allows users to:

Select difficulty level and topic

Fetch pre-stored questions from a dataset

Generate new AI-based quiz questions dynamically

View correct answers with explanations

ğŸ§  Key Features

âœ… Local AI inference (No API / No Internet required)

âœ… Small Language Model (TinyLlama-1.1B)

âœ… Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)

âœ… Difficulty-wise and topic-wise question generation

âœ… CPU & GPU auto-detection

âœ… Clean and interactive UI using Streamlit

âœ… Educational & privacy-friendly architecture

