âš™ï¸ How the Project Works
1ï¸âƒ£ User Interaction

User logs into the system

Selects difficulty level (Easy / Medium / Hard)

Selects a DSA topic

2ï¸âƒ£ Dataset-Based Retrieval

The system loads a structured CSV dataset containing:

Questions

Difficulty levels

Topics

Correct answers

Explanations

A random question can be fetched directly from the dataset for practice.

3ï¸âƒ£ Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)

When the user chooses â€œGenerate New AI Questionâ€:

A relevant example question is retrieved from the dataset

This example is added as context to the prompt

The prompt is passed to the local SLM

This improves:

Accuracy

Topic relevance

Question quality

4ï¸âƒ£ Small Language Model (SLM) Inference

Model Used: TinyLlama/TinyLlama-1.1B-Chat

Runs locally on:

GPU (if available)

CPU (fallback mode)

Uses Hugging Face transformers pipeline

Generates:

New question

4 options

Correct answer

Short explanation

5ï¸âƒ£ Output Parsing & Display

The AI output is parsed into structured fields

Displayed cleanly in the UI

Answer and explanation are hidden under an expandable section

ğŸ§© Technologies Used
Component	Technology
Frontend	Streamlit
Backend	Python
AI Model	TinyLlama-1.1B (SLM)
ML Framework	Hugging Face Transformers
Hardware Support	CPU / CUDA GPU
Data Storage	CSV
Optimization	Caching & Device Auto-Detection
ğŸ†š Why Small Language Model (SLM)?
Aspect	SLM	LLM
Deployment	Local	Cloud
Cost	Free	Expensive
Latency	Low	High
Privacy	High	Low
Hardware	Low-end friendly	High-end required

This makes SLMs ideal for academic projects and private AI systems.

